---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
	title="Burnout Is Not Failure: A Letter to Every Parent Carer | OAKonsult"
	description="You didn't burn out because you are weak. You burned out because you have been carrying more than most people can see."
	path="/blog/burnout-is-not-failure"
>
	<article>
		<section class="hero">
			<div class="container" style="max-width: 780px;">
				<p class="section-kicker reveal">Blog &middot; February 16, 2026</p>
				<h1 class="reveal" style="--delay: 0.05s;">Burnout Is Not Failure</h1>
				<p class="muted-copy reveal" style="--delay: 0.08s;">
					A letter to every parent carer who feels they're not coping well enough.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="section">
			<div class="container" style="max-width: 780px;">
				<img
					src="/media/wp/2022/09/oak-images-3.png"
					alt="Parent carer with child"
					style="width: 100%; border-radius: var(--radius); aspect-ratio: 16/9; object-fit: cover; margin-bottom: 2rem;"
					class="reveal"
					loading="lazy"
				/>
				<div class="reveal" style="--delay: 0.05s">
					<p style="color: var(--oak-muted); line-height: 1.9; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; font-size: var(--text-lead); font-style: italic;">
						Dear Parent Carer &mdash; burnout is not failure.
					</p>

					<p style="color: var(--oak-muted); line-height: 1.9; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
						So many of you are walking around believing you're not coping well enough.
						Not strong enough. Not organised enough.
					</p>

					<p style="color: var(--oak-muted); line-height: 1.9; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
						When the truth is far more compassionate.
					</p>

					<p style="color: var(--oak-muted); line-height: 1.9; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
						You didn't burn out because you are weak. You burned out because you have been
						carrying more than most people can see.
					</p>

					<div class="callout callout--gold" style="margin: 1.5rem 0;">
						<p style="line-height: 1.9;">
							The appointments. The worry. The constant responsibility. The emotional weight.
							The sleepless nights. The fear about the future.
						</p>
						<p style="margin-top: 0.75rem; line-height: 1.9;">
							And somewhere in all of that &mdash; <strong>you disappeared</strong>.
						</p>
					</div>

					<p style="color: var(--oak-muted); line-height: 1.9; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
						Burnout is not a sign that you are failing your child.
					</p>

					<p style="color: var(--oak-muted); line-height: 1.9; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
						It is often a sign that you have been succeeding at survival for too long
						&mdash; without support.
					</p>

					<p style="color: var(--oak-muted); line-height: 1.9; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
						And survival was never meant to be your permanent state.
					</p>

					<p style="color: var(--oak-forest); line-height: 1.9; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600;">
						You deserve rest. You deserve clarity. You deserve to feel like yourself again.
					</p>

					<p style="color: var(--oak-muted); line-height: 1.9; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
						If something in you whispered "I need this" &mdash; trust that voice. Our programmes
						are designed to help parent carers move from surviving to living again.
					</p>

					<div class="callout-actions" style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">
						<a class="button button-primary" href="/projectme">Explore Project ME</a>
						<a class="button button-ghost" href="/support-for-parent-carers">Parent Carer Support</a>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
	</article>
</Layout>
